Tires
Pirelli
Italy
Ferrari and Pirelli have shared a deep-rooted paterhneship that dates back to the very inception of
Ferrari in 1947 (the 125 S was equipped with Pirelli tires). Over the years, Ferrari has also relied on
other tire suppliers (e.g. Michelin for LaFerrari) however Pirelli has very clearly been the partner of
choice. Today, Ferrari road cars are by default equipped with Pirelli tires. As for F1 cars, like all other
teams, Ferrari uses Pirelli tires (Pirelli is the offical sponsor and supplier of F1).
Fuels and
lubricants
Shell
The Netherlands
The parternship between Ferrari and Shell began as far back as 1929, when Enzo Ferrari founded
Scuderia Ferrai as a racing team. This relationship continued into the inaugural Formula 1 World
Championship in 1950, with Shell supporting Ferrari's entry into the series. After a hiatus between the
mid 1970s and mid 1990s, the collaboration has resumed in 1996.
Brakes
Brembo
Italy
Ferrari and Brembo have shared a robust and enduring partnership since 1975, when Enzo Ferrari
selected Brembo to supply brake components for Scuderia Ferrari Formula 1 cars (marking Brembo's
debut in F1). Over the decades, their partnership has been extended to road cars. Brembo also
supplies a very wide range of luxury and performance cars (Aston Martin, Audi, McLaren, etc.), as well
as mainstream and premium brands (e.g. Ford, Honda, Nissan, Tesla, etc.)
Carbon Fiber
Structures
Mitsubishi & CPC
Japan/Italy
Ferrari collaborates with several supecialized suppliers for carbon fiber materials and components,
integral to its high performance vehicule. These partnerships encompass both ra material providers
and manufacturers of finished carbon parts. We believe that the main supplier is Japanese Group
Mitsubishi Chemical, via its Modena headquarterd Italian subsidiary CPC (since 2017).We believe that
CPC's clients also include Lamborghini, McLaren, Maserati or BMW, among others. Other Carbon
suppliers to Ferrari include SGL Carbon, CBS Compositi and Hexcel Corporation.
Electronics &
Control Units
Marelli
Italy
Marelli has been a pivotal technical partner to Ferrari for several decades, particularly in the realm of
motorsport. The collaboration dates back to the 1970s, with Marelli supplying advanced electronic
systems to Scuderia Ferrari. Notably, in 1989, the two companies co-developped the semi-automatic
gearbox, a groundbreakding innovation in F1 at the time. Today, Marelli supplies equipes both Ferrari
F1 and road cars with technology such as engine control units, kinetic energy recovery systems or
powertrain control systems.
Interior &
Seating
Poltrona Frau
Italy
Poltrona Frau's Interiors in Motion division, established in 1984, specializes in crafting automotive
interiros. With a facility in Tolentino (Italy), the division today employs approximately 600 artisans.
Poltrona Frau has been a key supplier of leather interiors to Ferrari vehicles since 1995. PF's leathers
are crafted using a proprietary "Pelle Frau" leather, renowned for its durability and luxurious feel. The
leather undergoes a meticulous 21-step tanning process, ensuring it meets Ferrari's stringent quality
standards. Since 2014, Poltrona Frau has been a wholly owned subsidiary of US Group Haworth,
specialised in office spaces.
